    %h2.main-color.yellow WHAT IS BPM?
    
    %p "BPM" stands for "Beats Per Minute" and is the tempo of a piece of music. It is essential data for DJs as they mix together multiple tracks, as tracks that are not tempo-matched will sound out of sync. BPM also has implications on what genre a piece of music is, though  there is plenty of room for debate. Many times, people will argue that the BPM is either 1/2 or 2 times as fast as a stated BPM---it's all about the pulse, and we all interpret it a little differently. 
    
    %p Click on any of the blue dots on the meter to listen to YouTube videos of different BPMs.

